        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 4:24PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 423 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cuchara, or 38 miles east of San Luis Valley Airport, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail and torrential
rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible. Torrential rainfall could cause wash outs on
mountain roads.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern
Huerfano, east central Costilla and west central Las Animas Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
